<p>If value from last process has an abs: If value from last process has an absolute change from previous time it was calculated higher or equal to the specified value, processlist execution will skip the next process.
If value from last process has an absolute change from previous time it was calculated lower than the specified value, processlist execution will skip the next process.
<p>A time elapsed dependent condition, f: A time elapsed dependent condition, first time a processlist passes here the flow is unchanged. Next times the same processlist passes here, if the specified value time (in seconds) has not elapsed, flow will skip next process.

A time elapsed dependent condition, first time a processlist passes here the flow skips next. Next times the same processlist passes here, if the specified value time (in seconds) has elapsed, flow will skip next process.
